{"title_page": "Auriac, Aude", "text_new": "{{short description|Commune in Occitanie, France}}\n{{Infobox French commune\n|name                   = Auriac\n|commune status         = [[Communes of France|Commune]]\n|image                  = Auriac.JPG\n|caption                = The road into Auriac\n|image coat of arms     = Blason de la ville d'Auriac (11).svg\n|arrondissement         = Narbonne\n|canton                 = Les Corbi\u00e8res\n|INSEE                  = 11020\n|postal code            = 11330\n|mayor                  = Jean Simon\n|term                   = 2014-2020\n|intercommunality       = [[Communaut\u00e9 de communes R\u00e9gion L\u00e9zignanaise, Corbi\u00e8res et Minervois|CC R\u00e9gion L\u00e9zignanaise Corbi\u00e8res Minervois]]\n|coordinates            = {{coord|42.9322|2.4928|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n|elevation m            = 568\n|elevation min m        = 356\n|elevation max m        = 907\n|area km2               = 20.93\n|population             = {{France metadata Wikidata|population_total}}\n|population date        = {{France metadata Wikidata|population_as_of}}\n|population footnotes   = {{France metadata Wikidata|population_footnotes}}\n}}\n\n'''Auriac''' is a [[Communes of France|commune]] in the [[Aude]] [[Departments of France|department]] in the [[Occitanie]] region of southern [[France]].\n\nThe inhabitants of the commune are known as ''Auriacois'' or ''Auriacoises''.<ref>[http://www.habitants.fr/habitants_departement_aude_11.html Inhabitants of Aude] {{in lang|fr}}</ref>\n\n==Geography==\n[[File:Col de Redoulade.JPG|thumb|The Col de Redoulade]]\n\nThe commune is located in the [[Corbi\u00e8res (mountains)|Corbi\u00e8res]] some 35&nbsp;km south-east of [[Limoux]] and 15&nbsp;km east of [[Arques, Aude|Arques]]. Access to the commune is by the D212 road which branches from the D613 west of [[Mouthoumet]] and goes south through the commune by a tortuous route then continues south to join the D10 north-east of [[Soulatg\u00e9]]. Apart from the village there are the hamlets of Savugnan in the south-west and La Grave north of the village. The whole of the commune is rugged and heavily forested.<ref name=Google>[https://www.google.com/maps/place/Auriac/@42.9310833,2.4992009,3406m/data=!3m1!1e3!4m2!3m1!1s0x12b0272516ea5d3b:0x4078821166d32b0?hl=en Google Maps]</ref>\n\nMany streams rise all over the commune and flow northwards to join the [[Orbieu]] which flows through the commune from south-west to north to eventually join the [[Aude (river)|Aude]] near [[Raissac-d'Aude]].<ref name=Google/>\n\n===Neighbouring communes and villages<ref name=Google/>===\n{{Geographic location\n|width=auto\n|Centre    = Auriac\n|North     = [[Lanet]]\n|Northeast = [[Mouthoumet]]\n|East      = [[Massac, Aude|Massac]]\n|Southeast = [[Rouffiac-des-Corbi\u00e8res]]\n|South     = [[Soulatg\u00e9]]\n|Southwest = [[Fourtou]]\n|West      = \n|Northwest = [[Albi\u00e8res]]\n}}\n\n===Heraldry===\n{{Blazon-arms\n|img1=Blason de la ville d'Auriac (11).svg\n|legend1=Arms of Auriac\n|text=The official status of the blazon remains to be determined.\n\n'''Blazon:'''<br/>\n''Argent, a fesse fusilly of Azure and Argent.''\n}}\n\n==Administration==\n'''List of Successive Mayors'''<ref>[http://www.francegenweb.org/mairesgenweb/resultcommune.php?id=12793 List of Mayors of France] {{in lang|fr}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! From !! To !! Name !! Party !! Position\n|-\n| 2001 || 2014 || Yvette Fabre ||   || \n|-\n| 2014 || 2020 || Jean Simon ||   || \n|}\n(Not all data is known)\n\n==Demography==\nIn 2010 the commune had 32 inhabitants. The evolution of the number of inhabitants is known from the population censuses conducted in the commune since 1793. From the 21st century, a census of communes with fewer than 10,000 inhabitants is held every five years, unlike larger towns that have a sample survey every year.<ref group=Note>At the beginning of the 21st century, the methods of identification have been modified by  [https://web.archive.org/web/20130514005038/http://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/affichTexte.do?cidTexte=JORFTEXT000000593100&fastPos=1&fastReqId=2036940488&categorieLien=cid&oldAction=rechTexte Law No. 2002-276 of 27 February 2002] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160306074946/https://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/affichTexte.do?cidTexte=JORFTEXT000000593100 |date=6 March 2016 }}, the so-called \"law of local democracy\" and in particular Title V \"census operations\" allows, after a transitional period running from 2004 to 2008, the annual publication of the legal population of the different French administrative districts. For communes with a population greater than 10,000 inhabitants, a sample survey is conducted annually, the entire territory of these communes is taken into account at the end of the period of five years. The first \"legal population\" after 1999 under this new law came into force on 1 January 2009 and was based on the census of 2006.</ref>\n{{clear}}\n{{Table Population Town}}\n\n[[File:Population - Municipality code 11020.svg|frame|center|'''Population of Auriac''']]\n\n==Culture and heritage==\n[[File:Auriac Ch\u00e2teau.jpg|thumb|Ruins of the Chateau]]\n\n===Civil heritage===\nThe commune has one building that is registered as an historical monument:\n*The '''Ruins of a Chateau''' (11th century){{M\u00e9rim\u00e9e Icon}}<ref>Ministry of Culture, M\u00e9rim\u00e9e {{M\u00e9rim\u00e9e|PA00102545|PA00102545 Ruins of a Chateau}} {{in lang|fr}}{{Camera}}</ref>\n\n===Religious heritage===\nThe commune has one religious building that is registered as an historical monument:\n*The '''Chapel of Saint-Andr\u00e9''' (12th century){{M\u00e9rim\u00e9e Icon}}<ref>Ministry of Culture, M\u00e9rim\u00e9e {{M\u00e9rim\u00e9e|PA00102544|PA00102544 Chapel of Saint-Andr\u00e9}} {{in lang|fr}}</ref> The Church contains one item that is registered as an historical object:\n**A [[Cope]] and [[Chasuble]] (18th century){{Palissy Icon}}<ref>Ministry of Culture, Palissy {{Palissy|PM11002132|PM11002132 Cope and Chasuble}} {{in lang|fr}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Communes of the Aude department]]\n\n===External links===\n*[https://www.google.com/maps/place/Auriac/@42.9310833,2.4992009,3406m/data=!3m1!1e3!4m2!3m1!1s0x12b0272516ea5d3b:0x4078821166d32b0?hl=en Auriac on Google Maps]\n*[http://www.geoportail.gouv.fr/accueil?c=2.4928,42.9322&z=7.92265E-5&l=GEOGRAPHICALGRIDSYSTEMS.MAPS.3D$GEOPORTAIL:OGC:WMTS@aggregate(1)&l=ADMINISTRATIVEUNITS.BOUNDARIES$GEOPORTAIL:OGC:WMTS(1)&permalink=yes Auriac on G\u00e9oportail], [[Institut g\u00e9ographique national|National Geographic Institute]] (IGN) website {{in lang|fr}}\n*[http://rumsey.geogarage.com/maps/cassinige.html?lat=42.9322&lon=2.4928&zoom=13 ''Auriac'' on the 1750 Cassini Map]\n*[http://www.insee.fr/fr/themes/tableau_local.asp?ref_id=POP&millesime=2010&typgeo=COM&codgeo=11020 Auriac on the INSEE website] {{in lang|fr}}\n*[http://www.insee.fr/en/home/home_page.asp INSEE] {{in lang|fr}}\n\n==Notes and references==\n\n===Notes===\n<references group=\"Note\"/>\n\n===References===\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n{{commons category|Auriac (Aude)}}\n\n{{Aude communes}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Communes of Aude]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Commune in Occitanie, France}}\n{{Infobox French commune\n|name                   = Auriac\n|commune status         = [[Communes of France|Commune]]\n|image                  = Auriac.JPG\n|caption                = The road into Auriac\n|image coat of arms     = Blason de la ville d'Auriac (11).svg\n|arrondissement         = Narbonne\n|canton                 = Les Corbi\u00e8res\n|INSEE                  = 11020\n|postal code            = 11330\n|mayor                  = Jean Simon\n|term                   = 2014-2020\n|intercommunality       = [[Communaut\u00e9 de communes R\u00e9gion L\u00e9zignanaise, Corbi\u00e8res et Minervois|CC R\u00e9gion L\u00e9zignanaise Corbi\u00e8res Minervois]]\n|coordinates            = {{coord|42.9322|2.4928|format=dms|displa